1. High humidity contributes to the sensation of warmth, making the air feel warmer than its actual temperature.
2. High humidity causes sweat to evaporate more slowly, resulting in a feeling of stickiness and warmth.
3. Warm temperatures are a common cause of high humidity, as warm air can hold more moisture.
4. The combination of warm temperatures and high humidity creates a sensation of sweaty conditions.
5. High humidity makes the body feel warmer due to the reduced ability of the air to cool the skin through evaporation.